official_title: A joint resolution to authorize the continued use of certain lands within the Sequoia National Park by portions of an existing hydroelectric project.

summary.text: (Measure passed Senate, amended) Authorizes the Secretary of the Interior to permit the continued use of Sequoia National Park, California, lands for the Kaweah Project of Southern California Edison Company for ten years. Permits one renewal of such term. Requires that the appropriate congressional committees be given notice before a permit is issued. Prohibits project expansion beyond its current boundaries.
